HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 27
BY REPRESENTATIVE DICKERSON
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Livingston Parish Fire Protection District #4 for
establishing the first high school firefighter training program in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and recognize Livingston Parish Fire Protection District #4 for establishing the
3 first high school firefighter training program in the state of Louisiana.
4 WHEREAS, Livingston Parish Fire Protection District #4 has demonstrated
5 outstanding leadership and innovation in the field of fire service education and training; and
6 WHEREAS, the district has taken significant steps to prepare the next generation of
7 firefighters by creating and implementing the first high school firefighter training program
8 in the state of Louisiana; and
9 WHEREAS, this pioneering program provides high school students with the unique
10 opportunity to learn essential firefighting skills, develop teamwork and leadership abilities,
11 and gain hands-on experience in a profession dedicated to the protection of life and property;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, the program not only fosters civic responsibility and public safety
14 awareness among youth but also strengthens the future of the Louisiana fire service by
15 cultivating a well-trained, highly motivated pipeline of future firefighters; and
16 WHEREAS, Livingston Parish Fire Protection District #4 serves as a model for other
17 fire protection districts and educational institutions across the state, inspiring collaboration
18 between emergency services and schools to create lasting community impact; and
19 WHEREAS, the district is most deserving of the highest recognition for its
20 groundbreaking efforts in advancing fire service training and education for the benefit of the
21 citizens of Louisiana.
